#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.136"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.136:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.136:0.2"
msgid "14. Devadahavagga"
msgstr "14. At Devadaha"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 136. Paṭhamarūpārāmasutta → sagayhasuttaṃ (bj) | agayha (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.136:0.3"
msgid "136. Paṭhamarūpārāmasutta"
msgstr "136. Liking Sights (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.127"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:1.1"
msgid "“Rūpārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā rūparatā rūpasammuditā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, gods and humans like sights, they love them and enjoy them."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.2"
msgid "Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"But when sights perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in "
"suffering."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.3"
msgid "Saddārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā saddaratā saddasammuditā."
msgstr "Gods and humans like sounds …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.4"
msgid "Saddavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.5"
msgid "Gandhārāmā …"
msgstr "smells …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.6"
msgid "rasārāmā …"
msgstr "tastes …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.7"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbārāmā …"
msgstr "touches …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.8"
msgid "dhammārāmā, bhikkhave, devamanussā dhammaratā dhammasammuditā."
msgstr "thoughts, they love them and enjoy them."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.9"
msgid "Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā dukkhā, bhikkhave, devamanussā viharanti."
msgstr ""
"But when thoughts perish, fade away, and cease, gods and humans live in "
"suffering."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.10"
msgid ""
"Tathāgato ca kho, bhikkhave, arahaṃ sammāsambuddho rūpānaṃ samudayañca "
"atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ viditvā na "
"rūpārāmo na rūparato na rūpasammudito."
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, "
"drawback, and escape of sights, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.11"
msgid "Rūpavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati."
msgstr ""
"When sights perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.12"
msgid "Saddānaṃ …"
msgstr ""
"The Realized One has truly understood the origin, ending, gratification, "
"drawback, and escape of sounds …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.13"
msgid "gandhānaṃ …"
msgstr "smells …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.14"
msgid "rasānaṃ …"
msgstr "tastes …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.15"
msgid "phoṭṭhabbānaṃ …"
msgstr "touches …"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.16"
msgid ""
"dhammānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca "
"yathābhūtaṃ viditvā na dhammārāmo, na dhammarato, na dhammasammudito."
msgstr "thoughts, so he doesn’t like, love, or enjoy them."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.17"
msgid "Dhammavipariṇāmavirāganirodhā sukho, bhikkhave, tathāgato viharati”."
msgstr ""
"When thoughts perish, fade away, and cease, the Realized One lives happily.”"

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.18"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "sn35.136:1.19"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvāna sugato athāparaṃ etadavoca satthā:"
msgstr "Then the Holy One, the Teacher, went on to say:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:2.1"
msgid "“Rūpā saddā rasā gandhā,"
msgstr "“Sights, sounds, tastes, smells,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:2.2"
msgid "phassā dhammā ca kevalā;"
msgstr "touches and thoughts, the lot of them—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:2.3"
msgid "Iṭṭhā kantā manāpā ca,"
msgstr "they’re likable, desirable, and pleasurable"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:2.4"
msgid "yāvatatthīti vuccati."
msgstr "as long as you can say that they exist."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:3.1"
msgid "Sadevakassa lokassa,"
msgstr "In all the world with its gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:3.2"
msgid "ete vo sukhasammatā;"
msgstr "this is reckoned as happiness."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:3.3"
msgid "Yattha cete nirujjhanti,"
msgstr "And where they cease"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:3.4"
msgid "taṃ tesaṃ dukkhasammataṃ."
msgstr "this is reckoned as suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
#. VAR: Sukhaṃ → sukhanti (bj) | sukhaṃ ca (s1-3)
msgctxt "sn35.136:4.1"
msgid "Sukhaṃ diṭṭhamariyebhi,"
msgstr "The noble ones have seen that happiness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:4.2"
msgid "sakkāyassa nirodhanaṃ;"
msgstr "is the cessation of identity."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:4.3"
msgid "Paccanīkamidaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "Those who see"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:4.4"
msgid "sabbalokena passataṃ."
msgstr "contradict the whole world."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:5.1"
msgid "Yaṃ pare sukhato āhu,"
msgstr "What others say is happiness"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:5.2"
msgid "tadariyā āhu dukkhato;"
msgstr "the noble ones say is suffering."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:5.3"
msgid "Yaṃ pare dukkhato āhu,"
msgstr "What others say is suffering"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:5.4"
msgid "tadariyā sukhato vidū."
msgstr "the noble ones say is happiness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:6.1"
msgid "Passa dhammaṃ durājānaṃ,"
msgstr "See, this teaching is hard to understand,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:6.2"
msgid "sammūḷhettha aviddasu;"
msgstr "it confuses the ignorant."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:6.3"
msgid "Nivutānaṃ tamo hoti,"
msgstr "Those who don’t see are closed off;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:6.4"
msgid "andhakāro apassataṃ."
msgstr "for them, all is blind darkness."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.128"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:7.1"
msgid "Satañca vivaṭaṃ hoti,"
msgstr "But those who see are open;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:7.2"
msgid "āloko passatāmiva;"
msgstr "for the good, it is light."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:7.3"
msgid "Santike na vijānanti,"
msgstr "Though it’s right there, the unskilled fools"

# Reading maga (in previous line of translation)
#. <br>
#. VAR: maggā → magā (bj) | mahā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.136:7.4"
msgid "maggā dhammassa akovidā."
msgstr "don’t understand the teaching."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:8.1"
msgid "Bhavarāgaparetebhi,"
msgstr "They’re mired in desire to be reborn,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: bhavarāgānusārībhi → bhavasotānusāribhi (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.136:8.2"
msgid "bhavarāgānusārībhi;"
msgstr "flowing along the stream of lives,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:8.3"
msgid "Māradheyyānupannehi,"
msgstr "mired in Māra’s dominion:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:8.4"
msgid "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho."
msgstr "this teaching isn’t easy for them to understand."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.136:9.1"
msgid "Ko nu aññatra mariyebhi,"
msgstr "Who, apart from the noble ones,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:9.2"
msgid "Padaṃ sambuddhumarahati;"
msgstr "is qualified to understand this state?"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:9.3"
msgid "Yaṃ padaṃ sammadaññāya,"
msgstr "When they’ve rightly understood it,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.136:9.4"
msgid "Parinibbanti anāsavā”ti."
msgstr "they’re extinguished without defilements.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.136:9.5"
msgid "Tatiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
